HEADWORD: branched
<hw>branched</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>resembling a fork;
divided or separated into two branches; <as>as, long <ex>branched</ex>
hairs on its legs, on which pollen collects</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bifurcate, biramous, forked, pronged,
prongy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

